This paper deals with the problem of zero-shot recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a probabilistic model for zero-shot recognition, which involves learning latent embeddings of source and target domain instances. This makes it relevant to the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as well. The paper also mentions the use of dictionary learning, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) as well.
